1. Data Type Matching Success Criteria
Accurate Column Matching (100%):
Ensure that 100% of columns with the same data types across databases are correctly matched, even with different names.
Data Type Consistency Across Databases (95%):
Ensure at least 95% consistency in data types (e.g., dates, numbers) for corresponding columns across different databases.
Automated Data Profiling (100%):
Achieve 100% automation for schema extraction (data types, column names) from Snowflake and other databases to minimize manual intervention.
2. Similarity Checks Success Criteria
High Accuracy in Column Name Matching (85% Threshold):

Implement Levenshtein distance and match 85% or higher similarity between column names that refer to the same concept (e.g., "gender" vs. "sex").
Phonetic Similarity Detection (Soundex - 90%):

Identify at least 90% of phonetic matches between column names that are phonetically similar (e.g., "Name" vs. "Nme") using Soundex.
3. Statistical Tests (Chi-Square) Success Criteria
Accurate Categorical Comparison (p < 0.05 in 95% of Cases):

Ensure 95% of Chi-square tests performed on categorical variables (like "gender" vs. "sex") yield p-values indicating significant relationships (p < 0.05).
Comprehensive Coverage (100%):

Ensure 100% coverage of all relevant tables and columns when performing Chi-square and similarity analysis.
4. Performance and Scalability
Data Processing Efficiency (95% of Queries within SLAs):
Ensure 95% of data processing queries are completed within the defined Service Level Agreements (SLAs) using AWS EC2 compute resources.
Scalable Solution (80% Reduction in Manual Intervention):
Build a solution that scales to handle growing data volumes, with an 80% reduction in manual processing through automation.
5. Business Impact and Usability
Actionable Insights (90% Usability in Reports):

Ensure 90% of generated reports and visualizations (in QuickSight, Tableau, etc.) provide actionable insights for stakeholders.
Alignment with Business Goals (95%):

Ensure 95% alignment between the analysis results and the business objectives, contributing to better decision-making and outcomes.
